the previous one, all have matching y values, despite their opposite signs in

00:00:11.838 --> 00:00:18.441
x. Let's think about why this is. Well, one way we can rewrite y equals x to

00:00:18.441 --> 00:00:24.347
the 4th is y equals x squared squared. We can do the same thing for something

00:00:24.347 --> 00:00:28.278
like y equals x to the 6th. That can be written as y equals x to the 3rd

00:00:28.278 --> 00:00:32.232
squared. And we know that whenever we're squaring something it's going to

00:00:32.232 --> 00:00:37.309
involve multiplying that thing by itself. So if what's inside here, like x to

00:00:37.309 --> 00:00:42.364
the 3rd. In the case of y plus x to the 6th. Is negative, squaring it is going

00:00:42.364 --> 00:00:46.712
to make it positive. That means that any sine g/ differences in x. Are going to

