be cancelled out in y. So that helps tell us why, even when we move way over to

00:00:50.947 --> 00:00:55.132
the left. Way to the negative side of the graph. On the x axis. The general

00:00:55.132 --> 00:00:59.370
behavior of the graph of a polynomial with an even degree. Is going to match

00:00:59.370 --> 00:01:02.970
the behavior on the right side, because of that squaring action here. Now, if

00:01:02.970 --> 00:01:07.010
we had a more complex polynomial here instead of just y equals x to the 4th.

00:01:07.010 --> 00:01:10.690
The y values to these numbers might not line up exactly. They might not be

00:01:10.690 --> 00:01:14.366
